The defendant Yasmani G Quijada was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Credit Card-Fraudulent Use (<=$2500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.41(5)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Cover letter dated 06/06/16, from Atty Hetzel, attached to Notice of right to seek post conviction relief.
with Elements of criminal offenses to which plea is being entered.

Defendant Yasmani G Quijada in court with Attorney Ryan J. Hetzel.  Timothy Suha appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  James Larson appeared as interpreter and is sworn-in.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #1.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1.  State has not complied with victims rights legislation as this was not scheduled for a plea and sentence today.  Court adjourns for short time to see if the state can comply with victims rights.  Case re-called at 11:45 a.m.  All appearances remain the same.  State states they have now complied with victims rights.  Case proceeds to sentencing.  State makes statements/recommendations.  Attorney Hetzel makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  FINE:  $578.00 & $200.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid in 20 days, alternate 15 days jail if not paid)  

**Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department**

NOTE:  Court orders that $1,000.00 cash bail on deposit forwarded to Waukesha County District Attorney's Office for extradition costs.

Defendant Yasmani G Quijada in court with attorney Ryan J. Hetzel.  David John Behm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Alexandria Wirth appearing as interpreter for defendant.  State files an amended criminal complaint amending the charge to a misdeamenor.   NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED.   Interpreter available for next scheduled hearing.  Hearing scheduled for June 3, 2016 at 09:00 am.
Preliminary hearing on April 22, 2016 at 10:00 am.
COURT ORDERED A $1000.00 CASH BOND IN ADDITION TO A $2000.00 SIGNATURE BOND.  Defendant to have no contact with Kohl's Department store or Adam F listed in the Criminal Complaint.
